{
  "stem": "10829.2",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my mother, they had this sort of a gut feelings, or fifth sense, or ninth sense, whatever you want to call it.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And a few days-- a day or so before that, before the big sweep, they said, there's too many Jews in this-- [YIDDISH] We used to speak Yiddish, basically, still do.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And most of the stuff that comes to me was in Yiddish, because the talking, the thinking, and a lot of I interpret it first.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I think of what they said in Yiddish, and then I interpret it over.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But they basically what they said is, this is no good.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We've got to go.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We got to get split up, because we're going to-- so we ran away from that forest, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] actually, 9, 10 of us.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we went into this other forest.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they had a big sweep in there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And everybody that I know of-- there was still quite a few Jews.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "There must have been at least 100, 200 Jews in there that survived the-- the final ghetto.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But they were all killed, most of them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Because we went into this other forest, and we met up form some that were in this different [NON-ENGLISH], but from-- but relatives.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And that clan that survived lives in Cleveland now, [INAUDIBLE] and his clan.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We met them down there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Now, life in the forest was simple.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "You had to live like an animal, think like an animal, and try to survive off of the land.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Things that you learn when you're young.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And we had an unusual situation, where we had me, who was the oldest boy, and my uncle Ben, and Zeyde.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "My mother was-- was-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] my-- my mother was always preoccupied with my brother.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
